  - feature-engineering
  - hierarchical-classification
abstract: >-
  missdetect is a research codebase that classifies the missingness mechanism
  (MCAR / MAR / MNAR) of a univariate column from a tabular dataset. It
  combines statistical and discriminative features with LLM-augmented features
  (judge, context-aware, self-consistency) and uses a two-level hierarchical
  classifier (Level 1: MCAR vs non-MCAR; Level 2: MAR vs MNAR) with
  Group-aware cross-validation and Cleanlab-weighted training for robustness
  to label noise.
